  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Upon initial creation of the account in status app user is asked about the notification permissions. Once i decline them using this pop up I am not able to enable notifications even settings are set correct (from disabled to enabled).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nI want to receive notifications once the option is enabled in device settings\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nPush notifications are not received\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create account\r\n- Decline notifications when asked\r\n- Check the notifications are not sent (use another device)\r\n- Enable notifications and put the app on the background\r\n- Send one more message from second device to the first one\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly 19/03/2018\r\n* Operating System: iOS",
